2020 has been a landmark year for the smartphone industry in South Africa as a result of the launch of several local 5G networks. This has aligned with the launch of several flagship 5G smartphones by the world’s most popular smartphone makers. Beyond offering support for 5G, these smartphones offer improved performance and features – with particular focus being placed on these smartphones’ cameras, processors, and displays. MyBroadband has highlighted some of the best smartphones to be launched in South Africa in 2020 below. Apple’s iPhone 12 smartphones are always one of the highlights of the year in the smartphone industry, and the company did not disappoint in 2020. The iPhone 12 Pro Max is the top of the range smartphone from Apple and is powered by Apple’s latest chip – the A14 Bionic. It also boasts an impressive triple-lens camera and a 6.7-inch 2,778 x 1,242 OLED display. The iPhone 12 was announced in October, while preorders opened to the South African market in November. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-371357 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/iPhone-12-Pro-3-640x430.jpg" alt="iPhone 12 Pro 3" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/iPhone-12-Pro-3.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/iPhone-12-Pro-3-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/iPhone-12-Pro-3-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> The Huawei Mate 40 Pro+ is the best device you can get in Huawei’s Mate range of smartphones and offers a number of great features. It sports a 6.76-inch, 90Hz OLED display and is powered by the cutting-edge Kirin 9000 smartphone chip. The Mate 40 Pro+ also has a remarkable penta-lens camera system which comprises of a 50MP main lens, 20MP ultrawide, 12MP telephoto, 8MP zoom, and 3D depth sensor. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-372492 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Huawei-mate-40-Pro-2-640x430.jpg" alt="Huawei mate 40 Pro+" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Huawei-mate-40-Pro-2.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Huawei-mate-40-Pro-2-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Huawei-mate-40-Pro-2-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> The Huawei P40 Pro+ is the best smartphone in Huawei’s other flagship range and offers significant improvements over its predecessor – the popular P30 Pro. It uses a 6.7-inch, 3,160 x 1,440 OLED display that offers a 90Hz refresh rate – whereas the P30 Pro only had a 60Hz display. The P40 Pro+ is powered by the improved Kirin 990 chipset which crucially supports 5G. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-379216 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/p40-pro-plus-black-640x430.jpg" alt="p40-pro-plus-black" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/p40-pro-plus-black.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/p40-pro-plus-black-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/p40-pro-plus-black-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> The Samsung Galaxy Note 20 Ultra is the best device in the first of three Samsung flagship smartphone ranges. It has a 3,200 x 1,440, 120Hz OLED display – making it a great device for gaming. It is powered by the Exynos 990 chipset in South Africa and its impressive quad-lens camera system is headlined by a 108MP primary lens. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-374358" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Note-20-Ultra-5G-640x430.jpg" alt="Note 20 Ultra 5G" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Note-20-Ultra-5G.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Note-20-Ultra-5G-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Note-20-Ultra-5G-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> The second of Samsung’s two traditional flagship smartphone lines is headline by the Galaxy S20 Ultra. Like the Note 20 Ultra, the S20 Ultra also runs the Exynos 990 processor and boasts a quad-lens camera system headlined by a 108MP primary lens. This camera system can capture up to 8K video and offers up to 100x zoom – making it a remarkable and versatile photography device. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-336226" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Galaxy-S20-Ultra-5G-Headline.jpg" alt="Galaxy S20 Ultra 5G Headline" width="640" height="431" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Galaxy-S20-Ultra-5G-Headline.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Galaxy-S20-Ultra-5G-Headline-594x400.jpg 594w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Galaxy-S20-Ultra-5G-Headline-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Finally, the Galaxy Z Fold 2 5G was a much more impressive device than Samsung’s previous attempt – the original Galaxy Fold. Its folded display is 6.2 inches while the smartphone’s main display measures 7.6-inches, meaning it essentially doubles up as a tablet when unfolded. It also boasts impressive specifications – including a Snapdragon 865+ processor, 12GB RAM, and a triple-lens rear camera system. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-362808" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Samsung-Galaxy-Fold-2-5G-1-640x430.jpg" alt="Samsung Galaxy Fold 2 5G 1" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Samsung-Galaxy-Fold-2-5G-1.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Samsung-Galaxy-Fold-2-5G-1-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Samsung-Galaxy-Fold-2-5G-1-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />